---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us | Doctoral College UK" description="Learn about Doctoral College UK — our mission, accreditation, faculty, and commitment to advancing doctoral education for working professionals.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Who We Are</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 whitespace-nowrap">The Evolution of Doctoral College UK into Brenkley Doctoral College</h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-muted max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-4 text-left">
        <p>Doctoral College UK was founded in February 2020 and in recognition of its continued growth, international ambitions, and commitment to establishing a distinctive educational identity, Doctoral College UK (DCUK) has adopted the new name Brenkley Doctoral College. Following an extensive review of branding, heritage, and long-term strategic positioning, the College concluded that the name Brenkley offers a unique and memorable identity deeply connected to the history and character of the college and the region in the UK where it is based.</p>
        <p>The name Brenkley originates from the historic locality of Brenkley, situated between the communities of Brunswick Village, Seaton Burn, and Dinnington, an area renowned for its rich industrial and innovation heritage. For generations, the region was associated with Brenkley Colliery (Seaton Burn Colliery), one of Northumberland's longstanding coal mining operations, which contributed significantly to the economic and social development of the surrounding communities from the nineteenth century through to the late twentieth century.</p>
        <p>Brenkley itself has a much longer history, with records identifying it as a historic township within the ancient parish of Dinnington, while archaeological evidence demonstrates that the area has been inhabited for centuries.</p>
        <p>By adopting the name Brenkley Doctoral College, the institution seeks to honour the resilience, innovation, and industrious spirit that characterised the communities of Brunswick Village, Seaton Burn, Dinnington, and the wider Northumberland industrial heritage. The new name reflects both a strong sense of place and a commitment to building a modern international centre for doctoral education, research, innovation, and knowledge creation, while remaining proudly connected to the heritage of the region from which it takes its identity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Our Mission</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Forward-Thinking Doctoral Education</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">DCUK provides rigorous, flexible doctoral programmes designed for working professionals. We believe that academic scholarship and professional practice are not in tension — they are mutually reinforcing. Our programmes are built around that belief.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">We work with senior managers, educators, healthcare professionals, public sector leaders, and entrepreneurs who want to move beyond opinion and convention to generate knowledge that lasts. Knowledge that is grounded in evidence, shaped by theory, and connected to the real world.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Our teaching model is designed for people who cannot step away from professional life for three years. Study is structured around professional schedules, with intensive residential weekends, online learning, and one-to-one supervision that fits around your commitments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Practitioner Focus</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Every programme we offer is designed around the practical realities of professional life. Flexible scheduling, online delivery, and supervision from academics who have worked in industry.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Research Excellence</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">We uphold the highest standards of academic rigour. Our researchers produce work that contributes to peer-reviewed literature, policy, and professional practice alike.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">UK-Based, Global Reach</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Headquartered in the UK and operating under UK Quality Code standards, DCUK serves doctoral researchers across Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and beyond.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Community of Scholars</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">You join a community, not just a programme. Our annual Doctoral Symposium, peer learning circles, and alumni network ensure you are never researching in isolation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founded -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Our Story</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Founded to Serve Practitioners</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-4">Doctoral College UK was established in response to a clear gap in higher education: the absence of truly flexible, high-quality doctoral pathways for experienced professionals. Traditional universities, however excellent, were not designed around the lives of people with senior careers, families, and organisational responsibilities.</p>
      <p class="text-muted mb-4">Our founders — themselves practitioner-researchers with experience spanning business, education, healthcare, and public service — created DCUK with a different model in mind. One where supervision is a genuine intellectual partnership, where methods training is practical and purposeful, and where the doctorate is a tool for professional transformation, not just an academic credential.</p>
      <p class="text-muted">Since our establishment, we have supported over 200 doctoral researchers through to completion, contributed to the development of practitioner-research methodology, and built partnerships with organisations across multiple sectors. We remain an institution built for purpose, not for prestige.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accreditation -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Quality & Standards</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Accreditation & Recognition</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">UK QC</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">UK Quality Code</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">All DCUK programmes are designed in alignment with the UK Quality Code for Higher Education, ensuring academic standards and enhancement of student learning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">SCQF</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Scottish Credit Framework</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Selected programmes are credit-rated through the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework at SCQF Level 11, enabling recognition and progression within the UK credit system.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">GDPR</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Data Protection Compliance</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">DCUK is fully compliant with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018. We handle all researcher and applicant data with transparency and security.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Our Faculty</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">The Team Behind DCUK</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Prof. Stanley Oliver</h3>
          <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-3">Principal</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Stanley leads the strategic direction of DCUK and supervises researchers in management strategy and organisational leadership. He brings over two decades of experience in executive education and practitioner research. His own research focuses on strategic decision-making in complex organisations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Dr. Zahra Salimi</h3>
          <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-3">Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Zahra oversees the academic quality of all doctoral programmes and leads supervision for researchers in education leadership. A specialist in qualitative inquiry, she has published extensively on practitioner-researcher identity and the ethics of insider research.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Dr. Liz Blower</h3>
          <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-3">Academic Lead for Operations &amp; Finance</p>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Liz ensures that every doctoral researcher at DCUK has the pastoral, academic, and community support they need to thrive. Her research background is in qualitative approaches to wellbeing in professional education, and she leads on researcher welfare and peer learning initiatives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/supervisors" class="btn-primary">Meet the full team</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to take the next step?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Explore our programmes or speak with one of our team to find the right pathway for your research ambitions.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/programmes" class="btn-primary">View programmes</a>
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-outline">How to apply</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
